HEADWORD: Keelage
<hw>Keel"age</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>guillage</ets>, fr. <ets>guille</ets> keel; of German or Scand
origin. See 3d <er>Keel</er>.]</ety> <def>The right of demanding a duty
or toll for a ship entering a port; also, the duty or toll.</def>
<rj><au>Bouvier. Wharton.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

